<DATELINE>OCEAN CITY, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A drowning, a missing swimmer, and a boating accident that killed two people, injured five and left two men missing and presumed dead marked this seaside resort's Memorial Day weekend. Searches continued until Sunday night for a missing 16-year-old boy who apparently was caught by undertow Saturday afternoon, and for two men still missing from the boating accident late Saturday night, authorities said. One woman was killed when an 19-foot boat carrying seven passengers plowed into an anchored, 25-foot boat with two aboard about a quarter-mile north of <LOCATION> Ocean </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, said <PERSON> Ralph </PERSON> <PERSON> Parker </PERSON>, a <ORGANIZATION> Maryland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Natural </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Resources </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> spokesman. The seven were ejected into the water and none was wearing a lifejacket, authorities said. Searchers found the body of a second victim around 8 p.m. Sunday about 300 yards from the collision site, officers said. The two men still missing were presumed dead, officials said. `` Most of the injuries seem to be impact injuries,'' said Sgt. <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Bloxom </PERSON> of the Natural Resources Police. `` And there's a possibility some of them might not have known how to swim. Authorities would give no further details other than that a 23-year-old <LOCATION> Baltimore </LOCATION> woman died at the scene and five people were taken to hospitals. The names of all nine people were withheld until relatives were notified. Authorities confiscated both boats, but issued no citations pending completion of the investigation. The 16-year-old <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> boy was reported missing Saturday afternoon after he and a friend went swimming and were caught in the undertow. The friend reached shore and alerted lifeguards. A search by <LOCATION> Ocean </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> police, the beach patrol, t