_ in 1979. There has always been speculation the prelate came from a communist country. In all, the new cardinals come from 18 countries and include several Vatican-based officials. Among them are Archbishop <PERSON> Achille </PERSON> <PERSON> Silvestrini </PERSON>, who is equivalent to the <LOCATION> Vatican </LOCATION>'s foreign minister; Archbishop <PERSON> Antonio </PERSON> <PERSON> Maria </PERSON> <PERSON> Javierre </PERSON> <PERSON> Ortas </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> Congregation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Catholic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Education </ORGANIZATION>, and Archbishop <PERSON> Jacques </PERSON> <PERSON> Martin </PERSON>, prefect of the papal household. The session on June 28 will be the fourth held by <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> II </PERSON> since his election as pope in 1978. The last was in 1985.
