t embodies what I am today.'' <PERSON> O'Meara </PERSON>, 36, is a seasoned organizer, having worked on several gubernatorial and congressional campaigns. He was an aide to <PERSON> Snowe </PERSON> before taking a position in 1981 with <PERSON> Cohen </PERSON>, for whom he has served as campaign finance director. He now is in charge of the senator's six offices in <LOCATION> Maine </LOCATION> <PERSON> O'Meara </PERSON> said he favors reductions in the federal deficit, is pro-choice on abortion, favors the Equal Rights Amendment and wants action, not further study, to curb acid rain pollution.
