<DATELINE>ABOARD USS VINCENNES IN THE PERSIAN GULF (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The commander of this super-sophisticated warship says its presence in the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> gives <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials many new options, including reducing the number of <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION> vessels. `` I think that it really gives the tactical commanders here in the gulf an opportunity to pick and choose as they see fit,'' Capt. <PERSON> Will </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rogers </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON> said in an interview on the bridge of the 9,400-ton <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION>. The <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION> on was on its first trip north through the gulf. Its arrival in the waterway was part of an extensive turnover in the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION>'s gulf-based force planned for the next several days. At least 10 ships are involved in the rotation, announced by the <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> in April. The San Diego-based <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION> is the first of the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION>'s billion-dollar Aegis missile cruisers to be deployed as a member of the <ORGANIZATION> Middle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> East </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> operating in the gulf The Aegis system is an array of powerful radars and missile weaponry linked with computers to enable a single ship to manage a widespread battle, carrying out dozens of radar surveillance and firing missions at the same time. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials have not explained why the <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION>, designed primarily for carrier battle group defense in the open ocean, is being assigned to the gulf, where its long reach and massive clout would appear to exceed any current threat posed to the <ORGANIZATION> Navy </ORGANIZATION>'s convoy escort operations or <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> interests Some <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION> officers and crew members say privately they are puzzled by the deploymen